 {"id":"franken_numpy-ol7l","title":"Match NumPy convolve same-mode length for longer kernel","description":"NumPy np.convolve(a, v, mode='same') returns length max(len(a), len(v)), not always len(a). Current UFuncArray::convolve_mode slices same-mode output to the first input length and the signal adversarial 'convolve_large_kernel' fixture mirrors that reduced behavior. Update convolve_mode to center-slice the full convolution to max(n, m), add unit coverage for longer-kernel same mode, and freeze the signal adversarial long-kernel fixture against NumPy's exact 64-value oracle output.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverBridge","created_at":"2026-04-18T13:26:33.437584526Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-19T21:33:53.459390674Z","closed_at":"2026-04-19T21:33:53.457034535Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","parity","signal"]}
